<h1>🏆 RS004 Week 16 — English Worksheet</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Title · Level Select · Sound · Showcase (Final) · <strong>Course:</strong> Platformer Game · <strong>Time:</strong> about 45 minutes</p>
<p>This is the final week. You built a finished game over 16 weeks: a <strong>title screen</strong>, a <strong>level select</strong> menu, and <strong>sound</strong> for jumps and coins, all running on a <strong>game state machine</strong> that moves between title → level select → playing → game over / victory. This worksheet is about reading and explaining that code in plain English, then presenting your finished game.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Keep these words handy: <strong>state machine</strong>, <strong>title screen</strong>, <strong>level select</strong>, <strong>sound</strong>, <strong>showcase</strong>.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
